♫ Only you can precisely capture ♫

15
00:01:10,528 --> 00:01:14,528
♫ Sour and sweet, the elusive taste of love ♫

16
00:01:14,528 --> 00:01:17,440
♫ Hey, what's on your mind, keeping you awake ♫

17
00:01:17,440 --> 00:01:21,600
♫ Tomorrow's work, and the planned trip ♫

18
00:01:21,600 --> 00:01:24,704
♫ How lucky I am that you've chosen me ♫

19
00:01:24,704 --> 00:01:30,496
♫ To share your present and your future ♫

20
00:01:31,136 --> 00:01:34,432
[VIP Only]

21
00:01:45,672 --> 00:01:46,739
Hey, boss.

22
00:01:46,739 --> 00:01:48,308
That person is here again.

23
00:01:49,776 --> 00:01:51,811
Why does he get to have it and I don't?

24
00:01:53,179 --> 00:01:54,747
Why are you so good to him?

25
00:02:13,032 --> 00:02:15,368
This is from my Boss.

26
00:02:15,368 --> 00:02:16,870
He asked me to prepare this

27
00:02:16,870 --> 00:02:18,671
for your hangover.

28
00:02:22,375 --> 00:02:24,110
I am so sorry

29
00:02:24,110 --> 00:02:26,146
for the trouble I caused last night.

30
00:02:26,846 --> 00:02:28,281
Yes.

31
00:02:35,321 --> 00:02:36,456
Tell me.

32
00:02:36,456 --> 00:02:38,525
Did you take a fancy to our boss?

33
00:02:39,726 --> 00:02:41,494
Didn't you two kiss yesterday?

34
00:02:41,494 --> 00:02:42,929
What exactly happened?

35
00:02:42,929 --> 00:02:44,931
And why didn't he go home?

36
00:02:46,466 --> 00:02:49,068
It seems I really was
a bit too drunk yesterday.

37
00:02:49,068 --> 00:02:50,170
I don't remember anything.

38
00:02:50,170 --> 00:02:51,771
You don't remember?

39
00:02:51,771 --> 00:02:53,540
Are you sure?

40
00:03:01,814 --> 00:03:02,916
May I ask,

41
00:03:02,916 --> 00:03:05,251
has Boss Gu always run a restaurant?

42
00:03:05,251 --> 00:03:06,853
Why are you suddenly asking that?

43
00:03:06,853 --> 00:03:09,222
Do you also think our boss doesn't
seem like a shop owner?

44
00:03:13,059 --> 00:03:14,427
Speaking of which,

45
00:03:14,427 --> 00:03:17,096
actually, our boss doesn't run this shop

46
00:03:17,096 --> 00:03:18,431
for money.

47
00:03:18,431 --> 00:03:21,201
He does it to carry on
the taste of his grandmother

48
00:03:21,201 --> 00:03:22,902
and to make every customer who comes here

49
00:03:22,902 --> 00:03:24,904
feel like they're home.

50
00:03:26,039 --> 00:03:29,509
He was once the leader
in the advertising industry.

51
00:03:29,509 --> 00:03:31,044
Do you know how many people were offering money

52
00:03:31,044 --> 00:03:32,946
for his creativity?

53
00:03:32,946 --> 00:03:36,015
Who knew he would be
affected by rumors and slanders?

54
00:03:36,015 --> 00:03:38,084
There were customers complaining

55
00:03:38,084 --> 00:03:39,819
about him being undutiful to his mother

56
00:03:39,819 --> 00:03:41,788
and the company offered compensation.

57
00:03:41,788 --> 00:03:44,657
Blah blah, so he left in the end.

58
00:03:46,025 --> 00:03:49,195
After leaving, it is as what you see now.

59
00:03:49,195 --> 00:03:51,164
He opened this store.

60
00:03:52,398 --> 00:03:55,368
But where did these rumors come from?

61
00:03:55,368 --> 00:03:56,672
This is the key point.

62
00:03:58,137 --> 00:04:00,240
If it wasn't for that woman…

63
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:01,541
Anyway.

64
00:04:02,308 --> 00:04:04,611
What? Boss.

65
00:04:04,611 --> 00:04:05,812
Why the big mouth?

66
00:04:05,812 --> 00:04:07,040
I didn't say anything.

67
00:04:07,814 --> 00:04:08,992
I'll go back to work.

68
00:04:29,769 --> 00:04:30,837
Drink this first.

69
00:04:30,837 --> 00:04:32,138
You will feel better.

70
00:04:34,107 --> 00:04:35,475
It smells good.

71
00:04:35,475 --> 00:04:36,542
What is this?

72
00:04:36,542 --> 00:04:37,977
Morning Bell Soup

73
00:04:37,977 --> 00:04:40,079
A sobering dish that has
the effect of relieving alcohol.

74
00:04:41,080 --> 00:04:43,008
After all, you did throw up a lot.

75
00:04:47,987 --> 00:04:49,022
I got you.

76
00:05:01,901 --> 00:05:04,203
I'm so wet.

77
00:05:14,314 --> 00:05:15,348
What's wrong with you?

78
00:05:29,862 --> 00:05:31,164
Are you okay?

79
00:05:52,285 --> 00:05:53,753
I'm sorry.

80
00:05:53,753 --> 00:05:55,888
I embarrassed myself so much yesterday.

81
00:05:59,225 --> 00:06:02,061
Just consider it as an extra experience.

82
00:06:02,061 --> 00:06:03,463
But I also kissed…

83
00:06:03,463 --> 00:06:05,231
If I cared,

84
00:06:05,231 --> 00:06:07,467
I wouldn't be standing here talking to you.

85
00:06:07,467 --> 00:06:08,868
Drink it quickly.

86
00:06:23,316 --> 00:06:25,351
Thanks for that Morris's autograph

87
00:06:29,989 --> 00:06:32,225
You should drink less in the future.

88
00:06:32,225 --> 00:06:33,493
Not only were you randomly kissing people,

89
00:06:33,493 --> 00:06:35,061
but you also brought up so much about yourself.

90
00:06:35,680 --> 00:06:37,920
I, I am really not like this normally.

91
00:06:44,837 --> 00:06:47,540
Why do you say you can't write the third book?

92
00:06:52,745 --> 00:06:57,049
The first book was to commemorate a confession.

93
00:06:57,583 --> 00:07:00,553
The second book was
to commemorate a heartbreak.

94
00:07:01,320 --> 00:07:04,674
For the third book, it seems
there's nothing worthwhile to commemorate.

95
00:07:04,674 --> 00:07:07,260
So, due to writer's block,
I can't write anymore.

96
00:07:10,930 --> 00:07:14,033
Do you think I should change my pen name?

97
00:07:24,076 --> 00:07:25,344
You'll find it.

98
00:07:26,208 --> 00:07:33,024
♫ Oh, it turns out happiness
is also good at disguising ♫

