When he is working,

105
00:08:03,683 --> 00:08:05,888
he rolls up his shirt sleeves to his elbows.

106
00:08:11,724 --> 00:08:13,392
That will be a total of 1500.

107
00:08:13,392 --> 00:08:14,794
Okay.

108
00:08:17,463 --> 00:08:20,199
He doesn't need a calculator
when settling the bill.

109
00:08:20,199 --> 00:08:21,601
He uses mental arithmetic.

110
00:08:31,277 --> 00:08:33,012
He is accustomed to using a pencil

111
00:08:33,012 --> 00:08:34,747
and his posture of holding a pen

112
00:08:35,248 --> 00:08:36,249
is very good-looking.

113
00:08:40,453 --> 00:08:41,587
Ren.

114
00:08:43,055 --> 00:08:45,858
You should get these things first tomorrow.

115
00:08:46,659 --> 00:08:48,027
Don't be lazy.

116
00:08:48,027 --> 00:08:50,329
Can only buy from the few stores I designated.

117
00:08:50,329 --> 00:08:51,864
Okay, no problem.

118
00:08:51,864 --> 00:08:54,600
He has his own ideas about cooking.

119
00:08:55,268 --> 00:08:58,170
But most of the time,
he only needs to tell others what to do.

120
00:09:05,344 --> 00:09:07,947
By the way, he also likes taking photos.

121
00:09:09,582 --> 00:09:12,051
I wonder what he sees

122
00:09:12,051 --> 00:09:13,853
through that viewfinder.

123
00:09:48,634 --> 00:09:51,446
