Wine & Dishes, Private Kitchen]

124
00:10:03,636 --> 00:10:05,071
Are you not writing anything today?

125
00:10:06,038 --> 00:10:07,872
My previous draft got rejected.

126
00:10:08,474 --> 00:10:10,112
have to find new inspiration,

127
00:10:11,110 --> 00:10:12,736
I don't have any ideas right now.

128
00:10:14,246 --> 00:10:15,424
Why was it rejected?

129
00:10:17,249 --> 00:10:18,284
The editor said

130
00:10:18,284 --> 00:10:20,653
the characters in my novels are too similar

131
00:10:20,653 --> 00:10:21,760
and they lack innovation.

132
00:10:23,255 --> 00:10:24,992
I don't know what to do either.

133
00:10:29,095 --> 00:10:30,240
Do you want some advice?

134
00:10:31,364 --> 00:10:32,768
Boss, are you helping him?

135
00:10:33,799 --> 00:10:35,801
Do you know how many people were offering money

136
00:10:35,801 --> 00:10:37,503
for our boss's advice?

137
00:10:37,503 --> 00:10:38,704
Consider yourself lucky.

138
00:10:39,905 --> 00:10:41,184
Offering money?

139
00:10:42,208 --> 00:10:43,342
So, is there a charge?

140
00:10:43,342 --> 00:10:44,384
Of course.

141
00:10:45,611 --> 00:10:46,712
Of course not.

142
00:10:46,712 --> 00:10:48,381
Does my boss look like someone

143
00:10:48,381 --> 00:10:49,600
desperate for money?

144
00:10:52,118 --> 00:10:53,184
There's no charge.

145
00:10:53,819 --> 00:10:56,489
But you can treat me to a late-night snack.

146
00:11:02,863 --> 00:11:06,272
[Original Fries]

147
00:11:31,123 --> 00:11:33,859
You said the characters in your works
were very similar.

148
00:11:37,296 --> 00:11:40,128
You were probably projecting someone
into your written characters.

149
00:11:41,600 --> 00:11:43,392
If you can't get rid of that,

150
00:11:44,236 --> 00:11:45,728
your characters will always be the same.

151
00:11:49,909 --> 00:11:52,645
If your creative inspiration comes
from your personal experience,

152
00:11:54,046 --> 00:11:56,384
you need to find another projection subject

153
00:11:57,249 --> 00:11:58,718
to escape your current dilemma.

154
00:12:08,461 --> 00:12:10,144
There are many ways to fold the bluebird.

155
00:12:10,996 --> 00:12:12,765
If you've never seen it before,

156
00:12:12,765 --> 00:12:15,234
you would think that the bluebird
only has one form.

157
00:12:17,737 --> 00:12:21,024
Of course, you might also know how to fold it,

158
00:12:22,274 --> 00:12:25,111
but you're scared to try
because of the difficulty.

159
00:13:15,928 --> 00:13:18,528
Find another projection subject?

160
00:13:23,969 --> 00:13:26,005
Where can I find that?

161
00:13:31,510 --> 00:13:33,184
There are many ways to fold the bluebird.

162
00:13:34,113 --> 00:13:35,840
If you've never seen it before,

163
00:13:35,840 --> 00:13:38,112
you would think that the bluebird
only has one form.

164
00:14:35,074 --> 00:14:36,096
Hello, Dad?

165
00:14:36,640 --> 00:14:38,464
Hey, Li, how's your job hunt going?

166
00:14:40,446 --> 00:14:42,715
I'm still writing novels.

167
00:14:42,715 --> 00:14:44,416
Didn't I send books back for you to read?

168
00:14:45,084 --> 00:14:46,496
Alright, we have received them.

169
00:14:47,036 --> 00:14:49,154
Have you made any money from your novels?

170
00:14:49,154 --> 00:14:50,289
Do you have enough?

171
00:14:50,289 --> 00:14:52,591
I do. You don't need to worry.

172
00:14:52,591 --> 00:14:55,027
The editor is rushing me
for drafts every day now,

173
00:14:55,027 --> 00:14:56,768
and I've also received
quite a bit of royalties.

174
00:14:57,430 --> 00:14:59,296
Alright, you should take good care of yourself.

175
00:15:01,567 --> 00:15:02,816
Okay. I have to go. Bye-bye.

176
00:15:24,690 --> 00:15:26,125
I've made the transfer.

177
00:15:28,294 --> 00:15:29,632
This is the last time.

178
00:15:30,829 --> 00:15:32,197
Don't call me again.

179
00:15:58,357 --> 00:16:01,293
How is the first step folded exactly?

180
00:16:08,500 --> 00:16:10,135
It's okay.

181
00:16:10,135 --> 00:16:12,871
I will learn it once he teaches
me a few times more.

182
00:16:22,272 --> 00:16:25,056
Could it be

183
00:16:26,880 --> 00:16:28,222
that I was stagnating?

184
00:16:34,226 --> 00:16:38,430
You need to find another projection subject

185
00:17:08,352 --> 00:17:10,997
Thinking that nothing can be replaced,

186
00:17:12,576 --> 00:17:13,952
but could it be

187
00:17:13,952 --> 00:17:18,240
that I forgot to put the right person in place?

188
00:17:33,157 --> 00:17:37,568
[The third Flavor]

189
00:17:55,841 --> 00:17:56,842
Jin.

190
00:17:57,676 --> 00:18:00,212
The story of the bluebird tells us

191
00:18:00,212 --> 00:18:02,881
that happiness is often right beside us.

192
00:18:03,682 --> 00:18:05,818
But only those who are willing to provide

193
00:18:05,818 --> 00:18:08,320
without seeking rewards can see it.

194
00:18:09,021 --> 00:18:12,124
If you blindly pursue distant happiness,

195
00:18:12,791 --> 00:18:14,860
no matter what color that bird is,

196
00:18:14,860 --> 00:18:16,995
it will be crushed to death in your hands.

197
00:18:16,995 --> 00:18:18,831
You need to take it easy.

198
00:18:18,831 --> 00:18:20,666
Don't be like your mother.

199
00:18:20,666 --> 00:18:22,418
Just wait patiently.

200
00:18:22,418 --> 00:18:25,237
The bluebird might have just gotten lost,

201
00:18:25,237 --> 00:18:26,638
and it will come.

202
00:18:44,957 --> 00:18:47,926
Luckily you guys weren't
thrown away from back then.

203
00:19:52,324 --> 00:19:53,525
Boss.

204
00:19:54,826 --> 00:19:56,328
What do you think?

205
00:19:57,763 --> 00:19:59,232
I'm trying a new recipe

206
00:20:00,199 --> 00:20:01,312
and let the customers do a blind taste test

207
00:20:03,335 --> 00:20:04,448
Boss.

208
00:20:05,248 --> 00:20:08,352
Haven't I always been a professional
for the taste-testing?

209
00:20:09,975 --> 00:20:11,040
You call it a blind test,

210
00:20:11,643 --> 00:20:13,745
but it must be served to Liu Li.

211
00:20:32,197 --> 00:20:33,728
Is this the taste of home?

212
00:20:35,534 --> 00:20:37,088
It is spot on.

213
00:20:56,321 --> 00:20:58,457
This looks so delicious.

214
00:20:59,925 --> 00:21:01,193
I'll dig in.

215
00:21:21,113 --> 00:21:22,304
Do you like it?

216
00:21:24,832 --> 00:21:25,884
I like it a lot.

217
00:21:25,884 --> 00:21:28,512
You see, I'm so busy eating
that I don't have time to talk.

218
00:21:33,892 --> 00:21:36,962
Every ingredient is exclusively special.

219
00:21:37,529 --> 00:21:39,097
If the food is not finished,

220
00:21:39,097 --> 00:21:41,099
the Chef will be very upset.

221
00:21:42,801 --> 00:21:43,802
Alright.

222
00:21:43,802 --> 00:21:45,760
Different vegetables for different people.

223
00:21:46,496 --> 00:21:47,680
Next time, I'll make what you love to eat.

224
00:21:55,647 --> 00:21:56,715
Happy birthday.

225
00:21:56,715 --> 00:21:58,950
I don't celebrate birthdays. It's not my thing.

226
00:21:58,950 --> 00:22:01,253
From now on, it can be your thing.

227
00:22:02,054 --> 00:22:03,622
The birthday person is the most important.

228
00:22:04,423 --> 00:22:05,457
Is there anything specific you want to do?

229
00:22:05,457 --> 00:22:08,627
Would you be willing to be
the reference for my third book?

230
00:22:18,432 --> 00:22:21,081
♫ I like ♫

231
00:22:21,081 --> 00:22:23,296
♫ The simple life with you ♫

232
00:22:23,296 --> 00:22:25,888
♫ A relationship without expectation ♫

233
00:22:26,601 --> 00:22:30,400
♫ Occasional distance allows us to breathe ♫

234
00:22:30,400 --> 00:22:33,952
♫ And occasionally more intimate than lovers ♫

235
00:22:33,952 --> 00:22:36,288
♫ It's getting late ♫

236
00:22:36,288 --> 00:22:38,496
♫ A couple of guests ♫

237
00:22:38,496 --> 00:22:41,120
♫ Are gradually leaving ♫

238
00:22:41,824 --> 00:22:45,280
♫ This dish is specially made for you ♫

239
00:22:45,280 --> 00:22:52,423
♫ Try it while it's still hot ♫

240
00:22:53,024 --> 00:23:01,056
♫ Stop talking, or the noodles will be cold ♫
